body: "Agents need an intuitive way to choose the next actionable pm item without reading every item body. Enhance pm-brief next with evidence-weighted explanations and confidence so project management stays context management while reducing token waste.\n\nImplemented evidence-weighted next-action ranking on 2026-06-12. Ranking now emits score, confidence, and compact evidence reasons covering priority, unblockability, active dependencies, fanout, stale age, linked docs/files, release, and deadline proximity. Added --explain and --confidence to pm brief next text output; JSON output includes structured ranking metadata. Verification: npm run release:check passed, and real CLI smoke test passed with pm install . --project followed by pm brief next --count 5 --explain --confidence --format json against this repo's pm data."
